charon.label: Charon
charon.description: Ancient ferryman of the dead. Gruff, impatient, menacing. White-haired demon with eyes like burning coals.

minos.label: Minos
minos.description: Judge of the damned. Monstrous figure who wraps his tail to indicate which circle souls descend to.

francesca.label: Francesca da Rimini
francesca.description: Tragic lover condemned for adultery with Paolo. Speaks with elegance and sorrow about their fatal love.

ciacco.label: Ciacco
ciacco.description: Florentine glutton lying in foul rain. Prophesies about Florence's political future.

plutus.label: Plutus
plutus.description: Demon of wealth guarding the fourth circle. Speaks in garbled, incomprehensible rage.

phlegyas.label: Phlegyas
phlegyas.description: Boatman of the Styx, consumed by perpetual rage. Father who burned Apollo's temple.

filippo_argenti.label: Filippo Argenti
filippo_argenti.description: Florentine aristocrat known for violent temper. Wallows in the Styx, attacks Dante.

fallen_angels.label: Fallen Angels at Dis
fallen_angels.description: Rebel angels guarding the gates of Dis. Defiant, proud, refusing entry.

furies.label: The Furies (Erinyes)
furies.description: Three hellish goddesses of vengeance - Megaera, Alecto, Tisiphone. Blood-stained, serpent-haired.

heavenly_messenger.label: Heavenly Messenger
heavenly_messenger.description: Angel sent to open the gates of Dis. Walks on water, scatters demons with a touch.

farinata.label: Farinata degli Uberti
farinata.description: Great Ghibelline leader, rises from burning tomb with proud contempt. Speaks of Florence's factions.

cavalcante.label: Cavalcante de' Cavalcanti
cavalcante.description: Father of Dante's friend Guido. Rises anxiously to ask about his son, collapses in despair.

chiron.label: Chiron
chiron.description: Wise centaur, tutor of Achilles. Leader of the centaur guards. Observant and thoughtful.

nessus.label: Nessus
nessus.description: Centaur who guides Dante through the river of blood. Killed by Hercules, killed Hercules in turn.

pier_della_vigna.label: Pier della Vigna
pier_della_vigna.description: Chancellor to Emperor Frederick II, falsely accused, suicide. Now a bleeding tree. Speaks in elaborate rhetoric.

capaneus.label: Capaneus
capaneus.description: Giant who defied Zeus at Thebes. Lies on burning sand still blaspheming, unrepentant.

brunetto_latini.label: Brunetto Latini
brunetto_latini.description: Dante's beloved teacher, scholar and statesman. Runs on burning sand but speaks with dignity and affection.

three_florentines.label: Guido Guerra, Tegghiaio, Jacopo Rusticucci
three_florentines.description: Three notable Florentine sodomites who run in a circle. Ask about Florence's state.

malacoda.label: Malacoda
malacoda.description: Leader of the Malebranche demons. Cunning, deceptive, gives false directions.

ciampolo.label: Ciampolo of Navarre
ciampolo.description: Grafter from Navarre, hooked by demons. Clever trickster who escapes by outwitting them.

catalano_loderingo.label: Catalano and Loderingo
catalano_loderingo.description: Two hypocritical friars from Bologna, founders of a corrupt religious order. Wear gilded lead cloaks.

vanni_fucci.label: Vanni Fucci
vanni_fucci.description: Violent thief from Pistoia. Blasphemes God with obscene gesture. Consumed and reformed by serpents.

ulysses.label: Ulysses
ulysses.description: Greek hero consumed by flame. Tells of his final fatal voyage beyond the known world.

guido_montefeltro.label: Guido da Montefeltro
guido_montefeltro.description: Military strategist turned friar. Deceived by Pope Boniface into giving evil counsel.

muhammad.label: Muhammad
muhammad.description: In Dante's view, a sower of religious schism. Horribly mutilated, split from chin to bottom.

bertran_de_born.label: Bertran de Born
bertran_de_born.description: Troubadour who divided father and son. Carries his severed head like a lantern.

master_adam.label: Master Adam
master_adam.description: Counterfeiter swollen with dropsy. Argues viciously with Sinon the Greek.

sinon.label: Sinon
sinon.description: Greek who deceived Troy with the wooden horse. Burning with fever, trades insults with Master Adam.

nimrod.label: Nimrod
nimrod.description: Biblical giant who built Tower of Babel. Speaks incomprehensible gibberish.

antaeus.label: Antaeus
antaeus.description: Giant who never fought the gods. Lowers Dante and Virgil into the final pit.

bocca_degli_abati.label: Bocca degli Abati
bocca_degli_abati.description: Florentine traitor frozen in ice. Refuses to give his name, Dante tears out his hair.

ugolino.label: Count Ugolino
ugolino.description: Count who gnaws his enemy's skull. Tells horrifying story of being starved with his children.

frate_alberigo.label: Frate Alberigo
frate_alberigo.description: Friar whose body lives while soul is in Hell. Murdered guests at his own feast.

cato.label: Cato of Utica
cato.description: Roman republican who chose death over tyranny. Guardian of Purgatory's shore. Stern but just.

casella.label: Casella
casella.description: Musician and Dante's friend. Sings one of Dante's poems, enchanting the newly arrived souls.

manfred.label: Manfred
manfred.description: Illegitimate son of Emperor Frederick II. Beautiful, wounded, excommunicated but saved at death.

belacqua.label: Belacqua
belacqua.description: Lazy friend of Dante, sits in shade doing nothing. Gently mocks Dante's climbing efforts.

pia.label: Pia de' Tolomei
pia.description: Murdered wife who speaks briefly and poignantly. 'Siena made me, Maremma unmade me.'

sordello.label: Sordello
sordello.description: Mantuan troubadour poet. Embraces Virgil as fellow Mantuan. Guide to Valley of Princes.

nino_visconti.label: Nino Visconti
nino_visconti.description: Sardinian judge, friend of Dante. Speaks sadly of his widow's remarriage.

angel.label: Angels of Purgatory
angel.description: Various angels who guard the terraces and erase sins. Speak blessings and guidance.

oderisi.label: Oderisi of Gubbio
oderisi.description: Famous illuminator bent under stone. Speaks of the vanity of earthly fame.

sapia.label: Sapia of Siena
sapia.description: Sienese woman who rejoiced at her city's defeat. Eyes sewn shut, purging envy.

guido_del_duca.label: Guido del Duca
guido_del_duca.description: Romagnol nobleman purging envy. Laments the moral decay of Romagna and Tuscany.

marco_lombardo.label: Marco Lombardo
marco_lombardo.description: Courtier in thick smoke of wrath. Gives important discourse on free will and corrupt Church.

pope_adrian_v.label: Pope Adrian V
pope_adrian_v.description: Pope lying face-down purging avarice. Tells Dante not to kneel to him.

statius.label: Statius
statius.description: Roman poet, secret Christian. Completed purgation, joins Dante and Virgil. Reveres Virgil deeply.

forese_donati.label: Forese Donati
forese_donati.description: Dante's friend, wasted by hunger on gluttony terrace. Exchanges memories and prophecies.

bonagiunta.label: Bonagiunta da Lucca
bonagiunta.description: Poet who recognizes Dante's new style. Asks about the 'sweet new style' of poetry.

guido_guinizelli.label: Guido Guinizelli
guido_guinizelli.description: Father of the sweet new style, Dante's poetic master. Purging lust in flames.

arnaut_daniel.label: Arnaut Daniel
arnaut_daniel.description: Greatest Proven√ßal troubadour. Speaks in his native Occitan, weeping and singing.

matelda.label: Matelda
matelda.description: Beautiful woman tending the Earthly Paradise. Guides Dante through Lethe and Eunoe.

piccarda.label: Piccarda Donati
piccarda.description: Nun forcibly removed from convent. First soul Dante meets in Paradise. Speaks of willing God's will.

justinian.label: Emperor Justinian
justinian.description: Byzantine emperor who codified Roman law. Tells history of the Roman Eagle.

charles_martel.label: Charles Martel
charles_martel.description: Young prince who died before inheriting kingdoms. Speaks of providence and heredity.

cunizza.label: Cunizza da Romano
cunizza.description: Much-married noblewoman known for love affairs. Now in Venus, speaks of her region's fate.

folquet.label: Folquet of Marseille
folquet.description: Troubadour turned bishop. Speaks of earthly love transformed to divine.

thomas_aquinas.label: Thomas Aquinas
thomas_aquinas.description: Greatest theologian, Dominican friar. Praises Francis, explains theological points.

bonaventure.label: St. Bonaventure
bonaventure.description: Franciscan theologian. Praises Dominic in return for Aquinas praising Francis.

solomon.label: King Solomon
solomon.description: Wisest of Hebrew kings. Speaks of the resurrection of the body.

cacciaguida.label: Cacciaguida
cacciaguida.description: Dante's great-great-grandfather, crusader knight. Prophecies Dante's exile with paternal love.

eagle.label: The Eagle of Justice
eagle.description: Collective voice of just rulers forming an eagle shape. Speaks of divine justice.

peter_damian.label: St. Peter Damian
peter_damian.description: Reforming cardinal and hermit. Denounces corrupt prelates from contemplative sphere.

st_benedict.label: St. Benedict
st_benedict.description: Founder of Western monasticism. Laments corruption of his order.

st_peter.label: St. Peter
st_peter.description: First pope, examines Dante on Faith. Later turns red with anger denouncing corrupt popes.

st_james.label: St. James
st_james.description: Apostle of Hope. Examines Dante on the virtue of hope.

st_john.label: St. John the Evangelist
st_john.description: Beloved disciple. Examines Dante on Love. So bright Dante is temporarily blinded.

adam.label: Adam
adam.description: First man. Answers Dante's questions about Eden, the first language, and original sin.

st_bernard.label: St. Bernard of Clairvaux
st_bernard.description: Mystical doctor, devotee of Mary. Replaces Beatrice as final guide, prays to Virgin.
